---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout region="uk" title="Services – Alturascope UK">
  <section id="services" class="py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Page header -->
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">
          Services
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-slate-600">
          U.K.-wide, decision-ready site reality.
          Every visit delivers clear visuals, accurate as-builts, and practical recommendations
          you can use immediately for design, budgeting, and approvals.
        </p>
      </div>
      <!-- Services grid -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <!-- As-Built Site Reality Visit -->
        <article class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <div class="flex-1">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
                As-Built Site Reality Visit
              </h2>
              <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
                Core service
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
              One visit to capture how the space actually is today.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">When you use it</h3>
                <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                  <li>New leases and renewals</li>
                  <li>Renovations, tenant improvements, change-of-use</li>
                  <li>Early test-fits and budgeting</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">What you receive</h3>
                <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                  <li>Digital twin you can walk through remotely</li>
                  <li>Photo storyboard of shell, core, MEP, ceilings, floors, and issues</li>
                  <li>Key dimensions &amp; counts (bays, doors, windows, washrooms, sprinklers, diffusers, lights, etc.)</li>
                  <li>
                    A detailed written conditions report with fixture counts and a high-level mechanical / services overview,
                    clearly highlighting both upside opportunities and concerns, prioritised into P1 / P2 / P3 so you know
                    what to act on first.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5">
            <img
              src="/Images/hvac.jpg"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/hvac.jpg';"
              alt="As-built site reality showing exposed HVAC and services"
              loading="lazy"
              class="h-48 w-full object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Construction Progress Visit -->
        <article class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <div class="flex-1">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
              <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
                Construction Progress Visit
              </h2>
              <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
                Progress monitoring
              </span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
              Independent eyes on your build, with photos and notes that track against the programme and pay app.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-700">
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">When you use it</h3>
                <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                  <li>Fit-outs and renovations in progress</li>
                  <li>Verifying GC draw requests and change orders</li>
                  <li>Hand-over readiness checks</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">What you receive</h3>
                <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                  <li>Fixed-route photo set for consistent, repeatable coverage</li>
                  <li>Progress notes by area (what’s complete, behind, or missing)</li>
                  <li>Exceptions / issues log with simple risk tags and suggested next steps</li>
                  <li>
                    A concise progress report that ties photos back to programme, pay applications,
                    and change orders, calling out risks, re-work exposure, and potential savings.
                  </li>
                  <li>Optional narrated walkthrough clip for remote stakeholders</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5">
            <img
              src="/Images/construction.jpg"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/construction.jpg';"
              alt="Construction progress night view"
              loading="lazy"
              class="h-48 w-full object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Portfolio & Lease Diligence Visit -->
        <article class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
              Portfolio &amp; Lease Diligence Visit
            </h2>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
              Multi-site
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Quick, consistent reality checks when you’re comparing buildings or locations.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">When you use it</h3>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li>Shortlisting buildings across multiple markets</li>
                <li>Renew vs. relocate decisions</li>
                <li>Pre-acquisition or pre-funding site checks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">What you receive</h3>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li>Comparable digital twin + photo set for each site</li>
                <li>Suitability summary: good fit / workable / problematic</li>
                <li>Call-outs on access, loading, parking, visibility, neighbours, and local quirks</li>
                <li>
                  A comparative diligence summary that highlights key upsides, constraints,
                  and hidden costs by site, so your team can line them up like-for-like and move quickly.
                </li>
                <li>“Red flag” list for anything likely to delay design, permitting, or opening</li>
                <li>Side-by-side summary table for shortlisted sites</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5">
            <img
              src="/Images/SING0469.JPG"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/SING0469.JPG';"
              alt="Portfolio diligence site photo"
              loading="lazy"
              class="h-48 w-full object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Stakeholder Walkthrough & Trade Day -->
        <article class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
              Stakeholder Walkthrough &amp; Trade Day
            </h2>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
              On-site representation
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
            A professional on-site representative to align brokers, clients, landlords, and trades
            around the same scope, budget, and reality.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">When you use it</h3>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li>Broker and client walkthroughs where decisions need to be made in the space</li>
                <li>Trade days to obtain accurate pricing and clarify scope</li>
                <li>When senior client stakeholders can’t travel but still need a trusted “face” on site</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">What you receive</h3>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li>Hosted walkthrough with brokers, client reps, landlords, and/or GC &amp; key trades</li>
                <li>Live clarification of structural, services, access, and base-build issues</li>
                <li>Field budget alignment and sanity checks on early pricing</li>
                <li>
                  A concise follow-up note summarising who attended, key agreements, open questions,
                  and any major cost risks or savings opportunities.
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
        <!-- Drone Photo & Video Layer -->
        <article class="flex flex-col rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm transition-colors hover:border-accent hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-accent/20">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-3">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900">
              Drone Photo &amp; Video Layer
            </h2>
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-slate-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-slate-700">
              Add-on
            </span>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Aerial context for roofs, sites, and surroundings – as an add-on to any visit.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-5 space-y-4 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">How it works</h3>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li>Added to any standard site visit (where local rules &amp; weather allow)</li>
                <li>Focused set of aerial photos and short video clips</li>
                <li>Not survey-grade mapping – purely visual, high-quality context</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-slate-900">What you receive</h3>
              <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                <li>High-resolution stills of roof condition, equipment, drainage paths</li>
                <li>Wide views of parking, access roads, loading, and neighbouring uses</li>
                <li>Short raw video clips for internal updates or investor/board decks</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-slate-500">
              Note: This is a visual photo/video service; U.K. drone regulations apply and flights are weather/airspace dependent.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-4 overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-900/5">
            <img
              src="/Images/drone%20shot1.JPG"
              onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='/images/drone%20shot1.JPG';"
              alt="Aerial drone photo of a commercial roof and parking"
              loading="lazy"
              class="h-48 w-full object-cover block"
            >
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
      <!-- CTA strip -->
      <div class="mt-12 rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 px-6 py-8 sm:flex sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900">
            Ready to move a site forward?
          </h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">
            Tell us where the building is, what decision you’re trying to make, and how fast you need an answer.
            We’ll recommend the right visit type and send a simple, all-in quote.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-3 sm:mt-0 sm:justify-end">
          <a
            href="/uk/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-slate-900 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-slate-800"
          >
            Talk to us about a site
          </a>
          <a
            href="/uk/pricing"
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-slate-300 px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-slate-800 hover:bg-white"
          >
            View pricing
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    </section>
</Layout>



